    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (78.03) and **Bryson Stott** (72.62) anchor the LawDog lineup as our primary producers. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** benefits from a high base projection and a favorable matchup against the lefty Liberatore, while **Bryson Stott** receives a significant 19% boost due to a soft matchup against Assad and advantageous wind conditions. **Geraldo Perdomo** (72.48) also warrants high confidence; despite the platoon disadvantage, his premium spot in the order and a massive +16% park factor adjustment make him a core contributor today. Keep a close eye on **Lawrence Butler** (60.61); while Eovaldi is a formidable arm\u2014dragging down the SP skill adjustment by 19%\u2014the combination of leadoff duties and favorable stadium dimensions keeps his floor high enough to justify the start.\n\nDeciding the bottom of the lineup proved difficult, with **Yainer Diaz** (40.13) barely cracking the threshold for active duty. The optimizer favored him over potential utility alternatives due to his base projection, but the matchup against a high-tier arm like Kirby makes him the most volatile element of the day. **Brendan Donovan** (58.77) and **Masyn Winn** (55.64) are functional, but their production is capped by stiff opposing pitching and park factors that negate their typical output. We continue to monitor the status of **Jonathan Aranda**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, **Gleyber Torres**, **Wenceel Perez**, **Gavin Sheets**, and **Drew Gilbert** to ensure we aren't leaving points on the table during roster rotation.\n\nRegarding the bench, the lack of active games for **Tyler Freeman**, **Matt Chapman**, **Daulton Varsho**, and **Luis Arraez** simplifies the decision, as these key assets are currently unavailable. The primary risk today lies in the volatility of the pitching matchups facing our middle-order hitters; specifically, **Will Smith** (57.93) and **Cal Raleigh** (53.71) are facing SPs with solid expected ERAs, which 